          <p>Michael Bertoldi graduated from the University of Regina in 1997 with a B.A. (Philosophy), and from UBC in 2001 with an LL.B.  After articling for a firm in downtown Vancouver, he founded Bertoldi and Company Legal services in 2002.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col s12 m8">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-content">
          <span class="card-title center">Areas of Practice</span>
          <h5>Collections:</h5>
          <bl>
            <li>
              Acting for creditors to recover on secured or unsecured debts inside and outside of B.C.
            </li>
            <li>
              Acting for judgment creditors to execute on Judgments obtained in B.C.
            </li>
            <li>
              Acting for judgment creditors from foreign jurisdictions to domesticate and execute upon their judgments
            </li>
            <li>
              Acting for debtors to resist collection measures or to assist in structured payments or settlements.
            </li>
          </bl>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <h5>Civil litigation:</h5>
            <bl>
              <li>
                Acting for plaintiffs or defendants in commercial or contractual disputes
              </li>
              <li>
                Acting for plaintiffs or defendants in real estate disputes
              </li>
              <li>
                Acting for strata corporations, management companies, owners, or tenants in condominium matters
              </li>
              <li>
                Acting for landlords or tenants in leasing disputes
              </li>
              <li>
                Acting for tradespeople or owners in builder’s liens disputes
              </li>
              <li>
                Acting for taxpayers in disputes regarding their taxes
              </li>
            </bl>
        </div>
